results.lead_paragraph: When I think of NASA photographs I think of those spectacular full-color reproductions in Life of the earth rising like a blue-andwhite bowling ball over the dun-colored surface of the moon, or those panormaic views of the rock-littered surface of Mars the color of pomegranate skin. I also think of pictures whose primary purpose is to show earth-bound stay-at-homes what distant and inaccessible places look like.
